HEADWORD: Prebendate
<hw>Preb"en*date</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>praebendatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>praebendari</ets>.]</ety> <def>To
invest with the office of prebendary; to present to a prebend.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Grafton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
